  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "CARPENTER",
  "description": "<p><!--td {border: 1px solid #cccccc;}br {mso-data-placement:same-cell;}--></p><p>Measure, cut, shape, and assemble wooden components according to blueprints or custom designs.</p><p>Operate woodworking machinery (e.g., saws, lathes, sanders) and hand tools safely and efficiently.</p><p>Perform sanding, polishing, and finishing to achieve required product quality.</p><p>Inspect and ensure the quality and precision of finished goods.</p><p>Repair or adjust products as needed to meet standards.</p><p>Maintain a clean and organized work area.</p><p>Follow safety guidelines and company procedures.</p><p>Collaborate with designers, supervisors, and other team members to meet production goals and timelines.</p><p>Proven experience as a Carpenter, preferably in household/kitchenware or furniture production.</p><p>Ability to read technical drawings and measurements accurately.</p><p>Skilled in using a variety of woodworking machines and hand tools.</p><p>Strong attention to detail and quality.</p><p>Knowledge of wood types, characteristics, and treatments.</p><p>Basic understanding of workplace safety procedures.</p><p>Good teamwork and communication skills.</p><p>Willingness to work night shift and split shift.</p><p>Willingness to work extra hours or weekend if needed.</p>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 5,
